<h1>Recamán's Sequence</h1>

<p>A visualisation of <%= link_to "Recamán's sequence", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recam%C3%A1n%27s_sequence" %>, with the option to apply the same process to starting sequences other than the integers. Inspired by a Numberphile video (see below).</p>

<label for="sequence-input">Base sequence:</label>
<select name="sequences" id="sequence-input">
    <option value="integers">Integers</option>
    <option value="primes">Prime numbers</option>
    <option value="squares">Square numbers</option>
    <option value="triangles">Triangle numbers</option>
    <option value="recamans">Normal Recamán sequence</option>
    <option value="fibonacci">Fibonacci numbers</option>
</select>

<br>
<br>

<canvas id="canvas"></canvas>

<br>

<div id="animate" class="btn btn-orange">Animate</div>

<br>
<br>

<label for="terms">Number of terms: </label>
<input type="range" min="10" max="255" step="1" value="31" class="slider" id="terms">

<br>

<label for="speed">Animation speed: </label>
<input type="range" min="1" max="10" step="0.1" value="4" class="slider" id="speed">

<br>

<div id="results"></div>

<div class="line-break"></div>

<div class="iframe-container">
  <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/FGC5TdIiT9U" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div>

<p>Note: I use a slightly different visualisation approach. Instead of the arcs alternating above and below the horizontal, I have them above for terms where the sequence is increasing, and below when decreasing.</p>

